LABEL: KE_ENGINE_SCHEDULE_RPM_HI
COMMENT: The engine speed above which some of the sync. code activation rate is changed.

LABEL: KE_ENGINE_SCHEDULE_RPM_LO
COMMENT: The engine speed below which some of the sync. code activation rate is changed.

LABEL: KE_ENGINE_IDENTIFIER
COMMENT: Describes the type of engine associated with the vehicle including the engine displacement and valve train geometry.

LABEL: KE_NUMBER_CYLINDERS
COMMENT: Number of cylinders for this engine application.

LABEL: KE_LOW_RESOLUTION_REFERENCE_ANGL
COMMENT: Identifies the number of degrees from a low resolution pulse to Top Dead Center of the cylinder.

LABEL: KE_TYPE_OF_KNOCK_SENSORS
COMMENT: Identifies whether the engine is equipped with resonant( 0 ) or flat response( 1 ) knock sensors.

LABEL: KE_AMBIGUOUS_CAM_TRANSITION_LOW
COMMENT: Cam sensor transition low limit based on 24X regions.

LABEL: KE_AMBIGUOUS_CAM_TRANSITION_HIGH
COMMENT: Cam sensor transition high limit based on 24X regions.

LABEL: KA_EGR_AIR_FLOW
COMMENT: EGR air flow through the EGR valve.

LABEL: KE_EGR_AIR_FLOW_FILT_COEF
COMMENT: The calculated EGRflow for Dyna-Air will be filtered using this coefficient.

LABEL: KE_EGR_DUTY_CYCLE_DYNAAIR
COMMENT: The commanded EGR duty cycle must be at least this value to enable calculation of EGR air mass.

LABEL: KA_VOLUMETRIC_EFFICIENCY_CRANK
COMMENT: Volumetric efficiency at cranking speeds.

LABEL: K_MAIN_VOLUMETRIC_EFFICIENCY
COMMENT: The volumetric efficiency term used for modeling the air per cylinder for Dyna-Air calculations.

LABEL: KV_GAMMA_INIT_COOLANT_BREAKPOINT
COMMENT: Breakpoints for selection coolant zone for initializing Filtered_VE_Correction_Factor.

LABEL: KA_GAMMA_INIT_TABLE
COMMENT: Initialize Filtered_VE_Correction_Factor to this value.

LABEL: K_CYLINDER_VOLUME
COMMENT: Volume of each cylinder in the engine.

LABEL: KE_BACKUP_AIR_FLOW_FILTER_COEF
COMMENT: Use this to filter air flow sensor reading to generate air flow 'prediction' in response to MAP OR TPS failure.

LABEL: KE_HI_SPEED_DYNA_AIR_THRESH
COMMENT: Engine speed above which a filtered value OF Sensed_Air_Per_Cylinder is used instead of the Dyna-Air prediction.

LABEL: KE_HI_SPEED_DYNA_AIR_HYSTERESIS
COMMENT: Amount by which engine speed must drop below KE_Hi_Speed_Dyna_Air_Thresh before the Dyna_Air prediction is used again.

LABEL: K_DYNA_AIR_COEFFICIENT
COMMENT: Array of corrective factors used to adjust the predicted volume of air that will get into the cylinder.

LABEL: K_INITIAL_OPERATING_ZONE
COMMENT: Initial engine operating zone.

LABEL: K_WIDE_OPEN_THROTTLE_LO
COMMENT: Minumum throttle percentage that is still considered wide open throttle.

LABEL: K_IDLE_VEHICLE_SPEED_HI
COMMENT: Maximum vehicle speed that is still considered idle conditions.

LABEL: K_IDLE_THROTTLE_HI
COMMENT: Maximum throttle percentage that is still considered idle conditions.

LABEL: K_ENGINE_SPEED_UPPER_BOUND
COMMENT: RPM boundaries between engine speed zones in the operating zones grid.

LABEL: KE_ENGINE_SPEED_HYSTERESIS
COMMENT: RPM boundary hysteresis for changing engine speed zones.

LABEL: K_MANIFOLD_PRESSURE_UPPER_BOUND
COMMENT: Pressure boundaries between manifold pressure zones in the operating zones grid.

LABEL: KE_MANIFOLD_PRESSURE_HYSTERESIS
COMMENT: Pressure boundary hysteresis for changing manifold pressure zones.

LABEL: K_MAXFLOW_SAFETY_FACTOR
COMMENT: A safety factor multiplied by the calculated maximum air flow limit used on the air flow variables used by the fuel logic.

LABEL: K_DEEP_DECEL_MAP_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: MAP threshold below which the engine is considered to be in deep deceleration.

LABEL: K_MODEL_OF_AIR_FILTER_COEF
COMMENT: Filter coefficient for the Model_Of_Air_Per_Cylinder term.

LABEL: K_STEADY_STATE_RPM_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: Steady state enable/disable threshold.  Used to determine if high MAP or low MAP conditions will be used.

LABEL: K_STEADY_STATE_MAP_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: Steady state enable/disable threshold.  Used to determine if high MAP or low MAP conditions will be used.

LABEL: K_STEADY_STATE_LOW_MAP_DELTA
COMMENT: If low MAP conditions, delta MAP must equal this to enter steady state.

LABEL: K_STEADY_STATE_HIGH_MAP_DELTA
COMMENT: Delta MAP criteria for enable/disable of steady state if high MAP conditions.

LABEL: K_STEADY_STATE_LOW_TPS_DELTA
COMMENT: Delta TPS for disable of steady state if low MAP conditions.

LABEL: K_STEADY_STATE_HIGH_TPS_DELTA
COMMENT: Delta TPS for disable of steady state if high MAP conditions.

LABEL: KE_IDLE_SS_INT_THRESH
COMMENT: Change in MAP integrator required to disable steady state IF engine is currently in the steady state condition.

LABEL: KE_IDLE_SS_MPH_THRESH
COMMENT: Vehicle must be < this to enable the idle steady STATE detection algorithm.

LABEL: KE_IDLE_SS_TPS_THRESH
COMMENT: Throttle position must be < this to enable the idle steady STATE detection algorithm.

LABEL: KE_IDLE_TRANS_INT_THRESH
COMMENT: Change in MAP integrator required to disable steady state IF engine is currently NOT in the steady state condition.

LABEL: K_VE_CORR_FACTOR_FILTER_COEF
COMMENT: Filter coefficient for Filtered_VE_Correction_Factor.

LABEL: K_VE_CORR_FACTOR_LOW_LIMIT
COMMENT: Lower limit of the Filtered_VE_Correction_Factor term.

LABEL: K_VE_CORR_FACTOR_HIGH_LIMIT
COMMENT: Upper limit of the Filtered_VE_Correction_Factor term.

LABEL: K_USE_MAX_AIR_FIRST_TIME_IN_1
COMMENT: TRUE if Air_Per_Cylinder 1 and 2 ahead are to be set to Maximum_Air_Per_Cylinder when zone 1 is entered.

LABEL: K_VE_CORR_FACTOR_RESET_THRESH
COMMENT: Reset Filtered_VE_Correction_Factor to 1.0 if it is less than this calibration when exiting deep deceleration.

LABEL: KE_EGR_DIAG_FINISHED_TIME
COMMENT: Dyna-Air learn is disabled during an intrusive EGR test and for this long after the intrusive EGR test has finished.

LABEL: KE_MAX_TOTAL_PUMP_TIME_ON
COMMENT: AIR system is forced off for the rest of this ignition cycle after being on for a total of this long in this ignition cycle.

LABEL: KE_AIR_DELAY_AFTER_START
COMMENT: AIR system is not allowed on until engine has run for this long.

LABEL: KE_AIR_ECT_DISABLE
COMMENT: AIR system is not allowed on at this time if coolant temperature is below this.

LABEL: KE_AIR_OVERRUN_DISABLE_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: AIR system is disabled when Manifold Pressure is < this AND remains diabled for KE_AIR_Extended_Overrun_Time thereafter.

LABEL: KE_AIR_HIGH_RPM_DISABLE_THRESHOL
COMMENT: AIR system is disabled when Engine Speed is > this FOR KE_AIR_High_RPM_Time and remains diabled until Engine Speed is <= this.

LABEL: KE_AIR_PUMP_TURN_ON_DELAY
COMMENT: Delay turning on AIR pump for this long after turning on AIR solenoid.

LABEL: KE_AIR_PUMP_TURN_OFF_DELAY
COMMENT: Delay turning off AIR pump for this long after turning off AIR solenoid.

LABEL: KE_BARO_DEFAULT_MAP_FAILED
COMMENT: Default barometric pressure used if MAP sensor fails.

LABEL: KE_BARO_TPS_LIMIT
COMMENT: Minimum throttle position to allow a part throttle barometer update.

LABEL: KE_BARO_TPS_DELTA_LIMIT
COMMENT: Minimum change in throttle position during last 100 mS to allow a part throttle barometer update.

LABEL: KE_BARO_MAP_DELTA_LIMIT
COMMENT: Maximum change in manifold pressure during last 100 mS to allow a part throttle barometer update.

LABEL: KE_BARO_STABILITY_TIME
COMMENT: Minimum time MAP and throttle must be stable to allow a part throttle barometer update.

LABEL: KE_MIN_RPM_FOR_BARO_UPDATE
COMMENT: Minimum RPM at which to allow a barometric pressure update.

LABEL: KE_MAX_RPM_FOR_BARO_UPDATE
COMMENT: Maximum RPM at which to allow a barometric pressure update.

LABEL: KE_MAX_BARO_OFFSET_FOR_UPDATE
COMMENT: Maximum calculated barometric pressure offset to allow baro update.

LABEL: KE_BARO_FILTER_COEFFICIENT
COMMENT: Barometer value update rate lag filter time constant.

LABEL: KV_BARO_OFFSET_FACTOR
COMMENT: Scaling factor used to correct the barometer offset value for altitude changes.

LABEL: KA_BARO_OFFSET
COMMENT: Sea level pressure offset to be added to the part throttle manifold pressure to correct the barometric pressure.

LABEL: KE_TRANSFER_CASE_RATIO
COMMENT: Transfer case gear ratio in 4WDLO for calibration application.

LABEL: KE_DRIVELINE_EFFICIENCY
COMMENT: Efficiency of transmission and axle gear multiplication for torque transfer.

LABEL: KE_TCS_FAIL_TRQ_ALLOWED_FACTOR
COMMENT: Scale factor applied to the Engine_Torque_Allowed parameterwhen traction control is known to be inactive.

LABEL: KE_BTM_RPM_OVERSPEED_ENABLE_LO
COMMENT: Once Brake Torque Management is enabled, engine speed must be at least this amount above desired idle speed to maintain BTM.

LABEL: KE_BTM_RPM_OVERSPEED_ENABLE_HI
COMMENT: Current engine speed must be at least this amount above desired idle speed to initially enable brake torque management.

LABEL: KE_BTM_TORQUE_HYSTERESIS
COMMENT: Hysteresis on the torque limit applied to prevent cycling in and out of limiting.

LABEL: KE_LOOPS_BETWEEN_RAMP_STEPS
COMMENT: Number of loops to wait between increases in the ramp out.

LABEL: KE_TORQUE_ALLOW_OFFSET
COMMENT: Torque offset below the maximum that will set the control target.

LABEL: KE_TORQUE_RAMP
COMMENT: Step size of torque when ramping out of brake torque management.

LABEL: KV_BRAKE_CAPACITY_VACUUM
COMMENT: This defines the maximum torque the vehicle brakes can absorb. It should be entered as an average torque for a single wheel.

LABEL: KV_COT_INC_TEMPERATURE_FILTER_CO
COMMENT: Filter used to predict current catalytic converter bed temperature when the predicted converter temperature is increasing.

LABEL: KV_COT_DEC_TEMPERATURE_FILTER_CO
COMMENT: Filter used to predict current catalytic converter bed temperature when the predicted converter temperature is decreasing.

LABEL: KV_COT_FFS_MULTIPLIER
COMMENT: Multiplier to compensate the stabilized temperature for any fuel composition effects on exhaust temperatures

LABEL: KV_COT_INITIAL_TEMP_SOAK_MULT
COMMENT: soak timer modifier for Converter temperature prediction

LABEL: KV_COT_VEH_SPEED_TEMP_OFFSET
COMMENT: A prediction of the difference in stabilized catalytic converterbed temperature relative to the speed of the vehicle.

LABEL: KE_COT_TEMPERATURE_INITIAL
COMMENT: If the coolant temperature is larger than this calibration, thenthe converter temperature is initialized to this calibration.

LABEL: KA_COT_TEMPERATURE_STOICH_STABLE
COMMENT: A prediction of the stabilized catalytic converter bed .temperature based on air-fuel ratio.

LABEL: KE_COT_THROTTLE_OPENED
COMMENT: Throttle position >= this allows immediate update OF catalytic converter temperature.

LABEL: KE_COT_THROTTLE_CLOSED
COMMENT: Throttle position <= this causes airflow to determine timing of catalytic converter temperature update.

LABEL: KE_COT_AIRFLOW_DELTA
COMMENT: Airflow dropping >= this IN one seconds causes delay OF catalytic converter temperature update.

LABEL: KE_COT_TEMPERATURE_DELAY_TIME
COMMENT: Overrun causes delay of this length in catalytic converter temperature update.

LABEL: KE_COT_HOT_DETERMINATION_ENABLE
COMMENT: COT hot determination is activated IFF this is TRUE.

LABEL: KE_COT_HOT_TIME_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: If the catalytic converter temperature is above KE_COT_Temperature_High for this time, then the converter is too high.

LABEL: KE_COT_TEMPERATURE_LOW
COMMENT: The lowest catalytic converter temperature protection threshold.

LABEL: KE_COT_TEMPERATURE_MEDIUM
COMMENT: The second catalytic converter temperature protection threshold.

LABEL: KE_COT_TEMPERATURE_HIGH
COMMENT: The third catalytic converter temperature protection threshold.

LABEL: KE_COT_TEMPERATURE_EXTREME
COMMENT: The Highest catalytic converter temperature protection threshold.

LABEL: KE_COT_MIN_EQ_ALLOWED
COMMENT: Minimum amount of fueling that COT will try to deliver. Have this minimum help to get back to closed loop fuel sooner.

LABEL: KE_COT_MAX_EQ_ALLOWED
COMMENT: Maximum amount of authority the COT EQ offset can have.

LABEL: KV_COT_INC_COEF_TEMP_DELTA_MULT
COMMENT: Multiplier on the COT increasing filter coeff based on delta between COT stabilized and 1 second old converter temperature.

LABEL: KE_CCP_COOLANT_TEMPERATURE
COMMENT: Coolant Temperature threshold above which purge may beenabled

LABEL: KE_CCP_VEHICLE_SPEED_FILTERED
COMMENT: Vehicle Speed threshold above which purge may be enabled

LABEL: KE_CCP_MASS_AIRFLOW
COMMENT: Mass Airflow threshold above which purge may be enabled

LABEL: KE_CCP_ENGINE_RUN_TIME
COMMENT: Continuous Engine Run Time threshold above whichPurge may be enabled

LABEL: KE_COOLANT_TEMPERATURE_STARTRUN
COMMENT: Coolant Threshold for determining purge enable delay startfrom closed loop entry.

LABEL: KE_COLD_START_CLOSED_LOOP_TIME
COMMENT: Purge Enable Delay after going closed loop if a coldstart occurred.

LABEL: KE_WARM_START_CLOSED_LOOP_TIME
COMMENT: Purge Enable Delay after closed loop if a warm start occurred.

LABEL: KE_CCP_COOLANT_STARTRUN
COMMENT: Coolant Threshold for determining purge enable delay from closed loop or open loop fuel control if selected.

LABEL: KE_CCP_COLD_OPEN_LOOP_TIME
COMMENT: Purge Enable Delay after engine run if a cold startoccurred.

LABEL: KE_CCP_WARM_OPEN_LOOP_TIME
COMMENT: Purge Enable Delay after engine run if a warm startoccurred.

LABEL: KE_CCP_OPEN_LOOP_PURGE_ENABLE
COMMENT: Bit selectable flag for purging when fuel control is in openloop. To be used primarily for exports without oxygensensors.

LABEL: KE_CYLINDERS_ENABLED_ALLOW_CCP
COMMENT: Number of cylinders that must be enabled to allowCanister Purge.

LABEL: KE_CANISTER_PURGE_OXYGEN_INITIAL
COMMENT: Initial Value of Oxygen Multiplier

LABEL: KV_CANISTER_OXYGEN_VOLTAGE_HIGH
COMMENT: High Oxygen Sensor Voltage threshold used to set the direction of Oxygen Purge Adjustment to decrease and the rate of learning.

LABEL: KE_CCP_MIN_OXYGEN_ADJUST
COMMENT: Minimum allowable value of the Canister_Purge_Oxygen_Adjustmultiplier.

LABEL: KE_CCP_OPEN_LOOP_OXYGEN_ADJUST
COMMENT: Default value of the Canister_Purge_Oxygen_Adjust factor whenpurge is being performed in open loop fuel control.

LABEL: KE_CCP_SHORT_DELAY_RATE
COMMENT: Short delay time between multiplier learns if oxygen voltage is high for a calibrated amount of time.

LABEL: KE_CCP_LEARN_RATE_NORMAL
COMMENT: Time delay between oxygen multiplier learns if the multiplier is increasing.

LABEL: KV_CANISTER_OXYGEN_VOLTAGE_LOW

LABEL: KV_GREEN_ENGINE_AIRFUEL_RATIO

LABEL: KV_HEATER_PERF_SPEED_OFFSET_DRIV

LABEL: KE_IGN_VOLT_TOO_LOW

LABEL: KV_MASS_AIRFLOW

LABEL: KE_MAX_RAM_FAIL_CTR_THRESHOLD

LABEL: KE_IGNORE_RAM_TEST

LABEL: KE_MAX_ROM_FAIL_CTR_THRESHOLD

LABEL: KE_IGNORE_FLASH_CHECKSUM
COMMENT: When TRUE the rom test results are ignored.

LABEL: KE_INDUCTION_AIR_TEMPERATURE_DEF

LABEL: KV_AIR_TEMP

LABEL: KE_OIL_STARVE_ENABLE

LABEL: KE_DRIVER_WARNING_DELAY_TIME

LABEL: KE_HIGH_G_MINIMUM_TIME

LABEL: KE_MINIMUM_VEHICLE_SPEED_FOR_OIS

LABEL: KE_MAXIMUM_VEHICLE_SPEED_FOR_OIS

LABEL: KE_OIL_SPEED_LIMIT_DECREASE
COMMENT: Delta MPH  decrease of ETC vehicle speed governor when engine oil starvation protection mode is enabled.

LABEL: KE_OIL_SPEED_LIMIT_INCREASE
COMMENT: Delta MPH  increase of ETC vehicle speed governor when engine oil starvation protection mode is NOT enabled.

LABEL: KE_THROTTLE_MAX_TO_RESUME_DRIVER

LABEL: KE_OIL_FILTER_COEFFICIENT

LABEL: KV_OIL_MIN_ENGINE_RUN_TIME

LABEL: KV_OIL_PRESSURE_DISABLE_LEVEL

LABEL: KV_OIL_TEMPERATURE_OFFSET

LABEL: KV_RESET_INTEGRAL_LATERAL_GS

LABEL: KA_OIL_BASE_LEVEL_LH
COMMENT: Left hand turn, threshold of Lateral G seconds, or an indication of amount of time spent as a function of G-forces

LABEL: KA_OIL_BASE_LEVEL_RH
COMMENT: Right hand turn, threshold of Lateral G Seconds, or an indication of amount of time spent as  function of G-forces

LABEL: KE_DEV_CNTL_O2_HTR_AIRFLOW_LIMIT

LABEL: KE_O2_HEATER_OVERVOLTAGE_LIMIT

LABEL: KE_PRE_O2_SENSORS

LABEL: KV_O2_HEATER_ROOM_TEMP_RESIST

LABEL: KA_O2_HEATER_DEGREES_PER_OHM
COMMENT: The change in degrees C per 1 ohm resistance change in the oxygen sensor heater for each sensor.

LABEL: KE_HIGH_SPEED_INHIBIT
COMMENT: Filtered engine speed above which PTO modes can not be established.  Also clamps PTO_Maximum_Engine_Speed.

LABEL: KE_HIGH_VEH_SPEED_DISENGAGE

LABEL: KE_PTO_HIGH_IDLE_ENABLED

LABEL: KE_HIGH_IDLE_BULB_CHECK_TIME

LABEL: KE_PTO_IDLE_ENGINE_SPEED_EEPROM

LABEL: KE_PTO_MAX_ENGINE_SPEED_EEPROM

LABEL: KE_RESUME_ENGINE_SPEED_EEPROM
COMMENT: Preset PTO engine speed when RESUME is pressed.

LABEL: KE_PTO_THROTTLE_AREA_LIMIT

LABEL: KE_HYSTERESIS

LABEL: KE_SCHEDULED_ACCEL_GAIN_UNDER
COMMENT: Underspeed scheduled acceleration rate gain.

LABEL: KE_PTO_ENG_SPEED_DELTA_HIGH

LABEL: KE_PTO_ENG_SPEED_DELTA_LOW
COMMENT: Acceleration error minimum value and maximum integrator decrement per 100ms.

LABEL: KV_GAIN_TABLE

LABEL: KE_PTO_ENG_SPEED_FILTER
COMMENT: Filter coefficient for engine speed for the PTO control algorithm.

LABEL: KE_PTO_EFF_SPD_ERROR_MAX

LABEL: KE_PTO_INTEGRATOR_GAIN

COMMENT: The tap up/down increment to memory speed and demand register.

LABEL: KV_ACCEL_STEP_FROM_ENG
COMMENT: An additional term added to the Demand Register at the initiation of an Accel in order to obtain more Desired Throttle Area.

LABEL: KV_RESUME_RATE

LABEL: KV_ACCEL_RATE
COMMENT: The accel rate increment per 100 ms.

LABEL: KE_COAST_RATE
COMMENT: The coast rate increment per 100 ms.

LABEL: KE_TAP_RATE
COMMENT: The tap up/down rate increment per 100 ms.

COMMENT: This calibration determines base spark 'bad fuel' contribution to spark advance.

LABEL: KE_AIR_PER_CYLINDER_BLEND_RATIO

LABEL: KE_HVS_RUN_MODE_DISABLE_RPM

LABEL: KE_LAUNCH_SPARK_MINRUNSOAKENABLE

LABEL: KE_LAUNCH_SPARKRPMMULTCOOLENABLE

LABEL: KE_LAUNCH_SPARKRPMRUNTIME

LABEL: KV_LAUNCH_SPARK_SOAK_MULT

LABEL: KV_LAUNCH_SPARK_DELTA_CYLAIRMASS

LABEL: KV_LAUNCH_SPARK_DELTA_CYLAIRMULT

LABEL: KA_EQ_RATIO_SPARK

LABEL: KA_EGR_SPARK

LABEL: KA_IAT_SPARK

LABEL: KA_RDSC_DAMPING_GAIN_OT

LABEL: KA_RDSC_PHASE_DELAY_TIME_CT

LABEL: KA_RDSC_PHASE_DELAY_TIME_OT
COMMENT: OPEN Throttle delay of the actual deliveryof active damping spark.

LABEL: KA_RDSC_SPARK_LIMIT_CT

LABEL: KA_RDSC_SPARK_LIMIT_OT
COMMENT: Limits the maximum absolute amount of RDSC active damping, when OPEN Throttle.

LABEL: KA_MAIN_CT_DRIVE

LABEL: KA_MAIN_CT_PARK
COMMENT: This calibration determines base spark closed throttle and park or neutral contribution to spark advance.

LABEL: KA_CLT_SPARK
COMMENT: Coolant temperature spark contribution.

LABEL: KE_EGR_SPARK_DELAY
COMMENT: The amount of time delay before enabling or disabling EGR spark.

LABEL: KE_EGR_DUTY_CYCLE_SPARK
COMMENT: The EGR duty cycle threshold that allows enabling or disabling of EGR spark.

LABEL: KE_RDSC_BLENDOUT_TIME

LABEL: KE_CT_VEH_SPD_THRESHOLD

LABEL: KE_CT_VEH_SPD_HYSTERESIS

LABEL: KE_SHIFT_PN_TO_DR_RAMP

LABEL: KV_ENG_PROTECTION_SPARK_ADVANCE

LABEL: KV_RDSC_STEADY_STATE_TPS

LABEL: KE_HVS_TEST_RPM_LO

LABEL: KE_CRANK_BLEND_STEP_OT

LABEL: KE_INITIAL_COOLANT_DEFAULT
COMMENT: Initial coolant default, used if IAT failed on powerup.

LABEL: KE_WARM_ENGINE_DEFAULT_COOLANT_M
COMMENT: Maximum value allowed for default coolant temperature.

LABEL: KV_DEFAULT_COOLANT
COMMENT: This is added to what the ambient air temperature was at powerup to determine what the default coolant temperature should be.

LABEL: KV_CYLINDER_AT_CAM
COMMENT: The cylinder number present when CAM has just transitionedto the indicated state.

LABEL: KV_SYNC_REFERENCES
COMMENT: Number of low-resolution reference pulses that must occur before a change in cam signal is assumed.

LABEL: KE_AC_CLUTCH_HIGH_FAIL_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: The number of failures required to set P1539

LABEL: KE_AC_CLUTCH_HIGH_PASS_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: The number of passes required to pass P1539

LABEL: KE_AC_CLUTCH_LOW_FAIL_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: The number of failures required to set P1546

LABEL: KE_AC_CLUTCH_LOW_PASS_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: The number of passes required to pass P1546

LABEL: KE_AC_PRESSURE_IN_FLT_TMR
COMMENT: The time that a failure must exsist to cause a fault to be displayed for AC pressure.

LABEL: KE_P0531_AC_PRESSURE_DELTA
COMMENT: The amount of PSI rise after AC compressor engagement, at all ambient temperatures, that indicates the sensor is not stuck.

LABEL: KE_P0531_AC_PRESS_ENABLE_TEST
COMMENT: When AC pressure is greater than this or when KE_P0531_IAT_Enable_Test is met, allow P0531 test to run.

LABEL: KE_P0531_IAT_ENABLE_TEST
COMMENT: When IAT is greater than this or when KE_P0531_AC_Press_Enable_Test is met, allow P0531 test to run

LABEL: KE_P0531_AC_HOLD_OFF_IAT
COMMENT: Hold AC compressor off for KE_P0531_AC_Off_Time when compressor turns off when IAT less than this.

LABEL: KE_P0531_AC_ON_TIME
COMMENT: The amount of time allowed for the AC pressure to rise the required delta before failing the P0531 diagnostic.

LABEL: KE_P0531_AC_OFF_TIME

LABEL: KV_AC_PRES_AD_CNT
COMMENT: When AC pressure is outside the window, then it is considered invalid.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_ENGINE_RUN_TIME_MIN
COMMENT: The minimum engine run time required to start the AIR diagnostic

LABEL: KE_AIRD_ACTIVE_CONTROL_WAIT_TIME
COMMENT: Minimum length of time before stopping the air induction request.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_ACTIVE_ENABLE_TIME_MIN

LABEL: KE_AIRD_ACTIVE_ENG_AIRFLOW_MAX
COMMENT: The maximum amount of engine airflow allowed during the active test.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_ACTIVE_ENGINE_LOAD_MAX

LABEL: KE_AIRD_ACTIVE_ENGINE_SPEED_MIN
COMMENT: The minimum engine speed required to run the active test.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_ACTIVE_LEAN_VOLT_MAX

LABEL: KE_AIRD_ACTIVE_TEST_TIME_LIMIT
COMMENT: Maximum amount of time allowed in the active test.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_ACTIVE_VEH_SPEED_MIN
COMMENT: The minimum vehicle speed required to run the active test.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_ENGINE_VACUUM_MIN
COMMENT: The minimum engine vacuum threshold to enable the passive and active tests.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PASV_AIRFUEL_RATIO_MIN
COMMENT: The commanded engine air/fuel control ratio shall be above this value for the passive test to run.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PASV_COLD_START_TEMP_LIM
COMMENT: Determines the powerup coolant temperature below which the passive test will be considered a cold start passive test.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PASV_ENG_AIRFLOW_MAX
COMMENT: Maximum engine airflow allowed during the passive test.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PASV_EXH_BACKPRES_MAX
COMMENT: Maximum engine load allowed during the passive test.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PASV_PART2_RICH_SAMP_MIN
COMMENT: Minimum number of rich samples required to pass part 2 of the passive test.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PASV_PART2_RICH_VOLT_MIN
COMMENT: Minimum O2 sensor voltage during part 2 of the passive test to consider the O2 sensor sample rich.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PASV_PART2_TIME_MIN
COMMENT: Minimum amount of time required for passive test part 2 to complete.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PASV_TEMP_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: Threshold to determine whether to use the cold or hot passive test logic.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PASV_TPS_DELTA_MAX
COMMENT: The maximum change in TPS values over 100ms interval allowed during the passive test.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PRETEST_DELAY_TIME
COMMENT: Amount of time necessary to complete the pretest delay.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PRETEST_FUEL_TRIM_MAX
COMMENT: The short term fuel trim variable shall be below this value to start the active test.

LABEL: KE_AIRD_PRETEST_FUEL_TRIM_MIN
COMMENT: The short term fuel trim variable shall be above this value to start the active test.

LABEL: KE_CAM_X_SHORTED_HIGH_CRANK
COMMENT: Limit of allowable high transitions when a hightransition should not have occured during crank state.

LABEL: KE_CAM_X_SHORTED_HIGH_RUN
COMMENT: Limit of allowable high transitions when a hightransition should not have occured during engine run.

LABEL: KE_CAM_X_SHORTED_LOW_CRANK
COMMENT: Limit of allowable low transitions when a lowtransition should not have occured during crank state.

LABEL: KE_CAM_X_SHORTED_LOW_RUN
COMMENT: Limit of allowable low transitions when a lowtransition should not have occured during engine run.

LABEL: KE_CAM_X_PERFORMANCE_CRANK
COMMENT: Limit of number of too many transitions occuringwhen only one transition should have occured duringcrank state.

LABEL: KE_CAM_X_PERFORMANCE_RUN
COMMENT: Limit of number of too many transitions occuringwhen only one transition should have occured.

LABEL: KE_CAM_X_SAMPLES_CRANK
COMMENT: Limit of number of samples for cranking.

LABEL: KE_CAM_X_SAMPLES_RUN
COMMENT: Limit of number of samples for engine run.

LABEL: KE_CAM_MISSING_SAMPLES
COMMENT: This many seconds of CAM transitions must be seen before reporting a Pass for the missing CAM signal diagnostic. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_CAM_MISSING_FAIL_LIMIT
COMMENT: If no CAM transitions are detected for this many seconds, report a Fail for the missing CAM signal diagnostic. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_CAM_SYNC_FAILURE_LIMIT
COMMENT: The number of failed tests within a sample size that will report a failure for the cam sync test. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_CAM_SYNC_SAMPLE_LIMIT
COMMENT: The number of tests that make up a sample size for the cam sync test. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_CAM_MAX_TEST_COUNTER
COMMENT: The number of times (engine cycles) to run the position test after the engine running flag is active. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_CAM_POSITION_MAX_DIAG_COUNT
COMMENT: The number of continuous position errors to qualify as a fault. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_CAM_POSITION_ERROR_MAX
COMMENT: Lower boundry multiplier for crank-cam pulse timing window. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_CAM_POSITION_ERROR_MIN
COMMENT: Upper boundry multiplier for crank-cam pulse timing window. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_CASE_FACTOR_MAX
COMMENT: Defines the threshold above which a cylinder compensation factor is considered to be too large.

LABEL: KE_CASE_FACTOR_MIN
COMMENT: Defines the threshold below which a cylinder compensation factor is considered out of range.

LABEL: KE_CASE_FACTOR_SUM_MAX
COMMENT: Defines the threshold beyond which the sum of the opposing cylinder pair compensation factors is considered to be out of range.

LABEL: KE_CASE_FACTOR_SUM_MIN
COMMENT: Defines the threshold below which the sum of the opposing cylinder pair compensation factors is considered to be out of range.

LABEL: KE_CASE_FAIL_TIMER_MAX
COMMENT: Defines the diagnostic failure threshold according to the activation rate specified herein for the owner process.

LABEL: KE_CASE_OPP_CYL_DIFF_MAX
COMMENT: Defines the threshold above which the opposing cylinder factors are considered to be too far apart.

LABEL: KE_LOSS_OF_MATCH_FAIL_LIMIT
COMMENT: Number of Loss of Match events required to report a Crank Sync Lost failure.

LABEL: KE_LOW_RES_REF_LOM_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: Number of low res ref pulses that must occur before Loss Of Match density is evaluated.

LABEL: KE_CRANK_SYNC_LOST_RATIO_LIMIT
COMMENT: Loss Of Match density (ratio of Loss OF Match events to low res ref pulses) that will report a Crank Sync Lost failure.

LABEL: KE_CRANK_SYNC_TEST_SAMPLE_LIMIT
COMMENT: Number of crank synch not achieved samples required to report test passed.

LABEL: KE_CRANK_SYNC_TEST_FAIL_LIMIT
COMMENT: Number of crank synch not achieved failures within a sample sample size required to report a crank synch not achieved failure.

LABEL: KE_MATCH_HAS_OCCURRED_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: This many matches in a single sample register as one crank synch not achieved failure.

LABEL: KE_MIN_CRANKING_MASS_AIRFLOW
COMMENT: Level of airflow when engine is cranking.

LABEL: KE_ACCELERATION_LIMIT_VALUE
COMMENT: RPM changes greater than this value over a 12.5ms interval must be faulty. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_MIN_RUNNING_MASS_AIRFLOW
COMMENT: Minimum airflow that indicates the engine is rotating and should be running. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_CRANK_INTERMITTENT_FAIL_LIMIT
COMMENT: Number of failed crank sensor tests for high acceleration out of a sample size that will report a failure. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_CRANK_INTERMITTENT_SAMPLES_LI
COMMENT: Number of samples that make up a sample size for the crank sensor test. Gen 1E only.

LABEL: KE_MIN_CAM_EDGES_AFTER_CRK_LOSS
COMMENT: If the crank sensor fails on a running engine, atleast this many cam edges must occur before setting a code. Gen IE only.

LABEL: KE_ECTR_ENGINE_AIRFLOW_MAX
COMMENT: Limit the value of engine airflow at this maximum.

LABEL: KE_ECTR_ENGINE_AIRFLOW_MIN
COMMENT: Airflow is set to zero, so that no airflow is accumulated below the mimimum.

LABEL: KE_ECTR_MAX_AMBIENT_TEMP
COMMENT: The maximum value that can be assigned to OBD_Intake_Air_ Temperature to represent ambient temperature.

LABEL: KE_ECTR_MAX_ENGINE_RUN_TIME
COMMENT: Maximum engine run time that will enable the test.

LABEL: KE_ECTR_MIN_ENGINE_RUN_TIME
COMMENT: Minimum engine run time that will enable the test.

LABEL: KE_ECTR_MIN_REQUIRED_IAT
COMMENT: Minimum intake air temperature value to enable the rationality test(s).

LABEL: KE_ECTR_MIN_VEHICLE_SPEED
COMMENT: Minimum vehicle speed value to update the distance measurement.

LABEL: KE_ECTR_MAX_ETH_PERCENT
COMMENT: The maximum fuel ethanol composition allowed to enable the test.

LABEL: KE_ECTR_TEST_FAIL_LIM
COMMENT: Number of consecutive failures without a pass to report a failed rationality test.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_ENG_RUN_TIME_HIGH_MIN
COMMENT: Minimum engine run time threshold to record a short to high fault.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_ENG_RUN_TIME_LOW_MIN
COMMENT: Minimum engine run time threshold to record a short to low fault.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_INT_SHORT_HIGH_FAIL_LIM
COMMENT: Number of failed intermittent short to high tests that will report an intermittent failure.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_INT_SHORT_HIGH_SMPL_LIM
COMMENT: Number of intermittent short high tests that make up a sample size.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_INT_SHORT_LOW_FAIL_LIM
COMMENT: Number of failed intermittent short to low tests that will report an intermittent failure.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_INT_SHORT_LOW_SMPL_LIM
COMMENT: Number of intermittent short low tests that make up a sample size.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_SHORT_HIGH_FAIL_LIM
COMMENT: Number of failed short to high tests that will report a failure.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_SHORT_HIGH_SMPL_LIM
COMMENT: Number of short high tests that make up a sample size.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_SHORT_LOW_FAIL_LIM
COMMENT: Number of failed short to low tests that will report a failure.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_SHORT_LOW_SMPL_LIM
COMMENT: Number of short low tests that make up a sample size.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_SHORTED_HIGH_IAT_MIN
COMMENT: Minimum IAT to enable an ECT shorted high failure prior to achieving sufficient engine run time.

LABEL: KE_ECTS_SHORTED_LOW_IAT_MAX
COMMENT: Maximum IAT to enable an ECT shorted low failure prior to achieving sufficient engine run time.

LABEL: KV_ECTS_SHORTED_HIGH_THRESH
COMMENT: The threshold above which the coolant sensor is considered shorted to a positive voltage.

LABEL: KV_ECTS_SHORTED_LOW_THRESH
COMMENT: The threshold below which the coolant sensor is considered opened or shorted to ground.

LABEL: KV_EGRF_ACHIEVED_POS_COMP
COMMENT: Compensation factor to reduce the delta MAP for high achieved positions.

LABEL: KV_EGRF_EWMA_COMPENSATION
COMMENT: Compensation factor to reduce the delta MAP for various restriction amounts.

LABEL: KV_EGRF_ON_TIME_COMPENSATION
COMMENT: Compensation factor to reduce the delta MAP for long on-times.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_ABORT_INTERVAL
COMMENT: Interval between test control assertions when the previous test was aborted during the intrusive period.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_AIRFLOW_DIFFERENCE
COMMENT: Maximum allowable difference between commanded and actual airflow during the TEST_STARTED mode.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_ALTITUDE_COMP_MAP_HIGH
COMMENT: Upper limit of range above which flow test is not run.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_ALTITUDE_COMP_MAP_LOW
COMMENT: Lower limit of range below which flow test is not run.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_BARO_MINIMUM
COMMENT: Minimum barometric pressure below which test may is not run.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_BASE_ON_TIME_COUNTER
COMMENT: Initial number of execution loops that the valve will be commanded open, after a powerup or a non-volatile init.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_CODE_CLEAR_ON_TIME_CTR
COMMENT: Initial number of execution loops that the valve will be commanded open, after an ALDL code clear.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_COMPLETE_INTERVAL
COMMENT: Interval between test control assertions, when the previous test was completed.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_DFCO_ENABLE
COMMENT: Condition for enabling flow mode test based on decel fuel cut off state.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_EWMA_FAIL_THRESHOLD
COMMENT: Threshold above which the diagnostic is considered failing,if the diagnostic is currently indicating a failure.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_EWMA_FAIL_COEF
COMMENT: Filter coefficient for EWMA calculation when test is indicating a failure.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_EWMA_NONFAIL_THRESH
COMMENT: Threshold above which the diagnostic is considered  failing if the diagnostic is currently not indicating a failure.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_EWMA_NONFAIL_COEF
COMMENT: Filter coefficient for EWMA calculation when test is not indicating a failure.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_EWMA_PASS_SAMPLES
COMMENT: Number of test samples required before the diagnostic can be considered passing.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_MAX_DELTA_MAP
COMMENT: Maximum range that MAP can fluctuate during test start period.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_MAX_DELTA_MPH
COMMENT: Max range that vehicle speed can fluctuate during the intrusive portions of the test

LABEL: KE_EGRF_MAX_NEG_RPM_CHANGE
COMMENT: Max negative change in engine speed allowed during the intrusive portions of the test.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_MAX_ON_TIME_COUNTER
COMMENT: Maximum number of execution loops the valve will be commanded open.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_MAX_POS_RPM_CHANGE
COMMENT: Max positive change in engine speed allowed during the intrusive portions of the test

LABEL: KE_EGRF_MAXIMUM_RPM
COMMENT: High limit of engine speed range to enable the flow test.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_MAXIMUM_TPS
COMMENT: TPS must be below this value to enable the flow test.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_MINIMUM_RPM
COMMENT: Low limit of engine speed range to enable the flow test.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_MIN_ON_TIME_COUNTER
COMMENT: Minimum number of execution loops that the valve will be commanded open,

LABEL: KE_EGRF_OVER_UNDER_COUNT
COMMENT: Number of consecutive overshoot or undershoot events necessary to modify the duty cycle on-time.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_OVERSHOOT_POSITION
COMMENT: Position above which the test will decrement the duty cycle on-time.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_RPM_COMPENSATION
COMMENT: Used to choose desired RPM compensation method. START_RPM = Starting RPM, MINIMUM_RPM = Minimum RPM during test

LABEL: KE_EGRF_SAMPLE_TIME
COMMENT: Amount of time the test is in the SAMPLE_CALCULATION mode.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_SAMPLES_PER_TRIP
COMMENT: Maximum number of samples per trip.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_START_MAX_POSITION
COMMENT: Maximum EGR starting position below which the valve is considered closed.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_STEP_DELTA
COMMENT: Minimum difference between MAPDIFF and EWMA to trigger multiple tests for step change

LABEL: KE_EGRF_STEP_MAPDIFF
COMMENT: Minimum value of MAPDIFF to trigger multiple tests for step change

LABEL: KE_EGRF_STEP_SAMPLES_PER_TRIP
COMMENT: Maximum number of samples per trip after a step change.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_TEST_ENABLE_DELAY
COMMENT: Length of time the throttle must be virtually closed before a flow test is allowed.

LABEL: KE_EGRF_UNDERSHOOT_POSITION
COMMENT: Position below which the test will increment the duty cycle on-time.

LABEL: KE_ESC_NOISE_RPM_HIGH
COMMENT: One condition to run the diagnostic is that engine speed be less than this cal.

LABEL: KE_ESC_CIRCUIT_ENG_RUN_TIME
COMMENT: If the engine run time is less than this value, then the test is to be bypassed.

LABEL: KE_ESC_CIRCUIT_FAIL_SAMPLES
COMMENT: Number of fail samples needed to report a fail in a sample period less than KE_ESC_Samples total.

LABEL: KE_ESC_CIRCUIT_SAMPLES
COMMENT: Number of samples needed before a pass can be reported.

LABEL: KE_ESC_COOLANT_TEMP_MIN
COMMENT: Minimum coolant temperature required to learn minimum noise.

LABEL: KE_ESC_FILTER_COEFF
COMMENT: Lag filter coefficient used in filtering the ESC noise channel.

LABEL: KE_ESC_INITIAL_NOISE
COMMENT: An initial startup value for filter purposes.

LABEL: KE_ESC_NOISE_ENGINE_RUN_TIME
COMMENT: Minimum engine run time before test can be enabled.

LABEL: KE_ESC_NOISE_LOW_COUNT
COMMENT: Number of successive low noise level conditions necessary to report a fail condition.

LABEL: KE_ESC_NOISE_LOW_LEVEL

LABEL: KE_ESC_NOISE_LOW_SAMPLE_COUNT
COMMENT: Number of samples before a low noise pass can be reported.

LABEL: KE_ESC_NOISE_HIGH_COUNT
COMMENT: Number of high noise level conditions per sample size necessary to report a fail condition.

LABEL: KE_ESC_NOISE_HIGH_LEVEL
COMMENT: High noise level threshold which must be exceeded a calibratable number of times to report a failure.

LABEL: KE_ESC_NOISE_HIGH_SAMPLE_COUNT
COMMENT: Number of passes needed before a high noise pass can be reported.

LABEL: KE_ESC_NOISE_RPM_LOW
COMMENT: One condition to run the diagnostic is that engine speed be greater than this cal.

LABEL: KE_ESC_NOISE_TPS_MIN
COMMENT: One condition to run the diagnostic is that Throttle position be greater than this cal.

LABEL: KE_ESC_RPM_MAX
COMMENT: Maximum engine speed to enable minimum noise learning.

LABEL: KE_ESC_RPM_MIN

LABEL: KE_FAND_SPEEDHI_SMPL_LIM

LABEL: KE_FAND_STABLE_SPEED_TIME

LABEL: KE_FAND_SYSPERF_FAIL_LIM

LABEL: KE_FAND_SYSPERF_RPM_MAX
COMMENT: Maximum allowable engine speed to enable the system  performance test.

LABEL: KE_FAND_SYS_SMPL_LIM
COMMENT: Number of samples required to pass the system performance test.

LABEL: KEFADD_B_FASD_DIAGNOSTICENABLED

LABEL: KEFADD_CNT_FASD_STABLESMPLCNTMIN

LABEL: KEFADD_CNT_FASD_WAITTIMEMAX

LABEL: KEFADD_DM_PURGENGAIRFLOWLOW

LABEL: KEFADD_N_FASD_PURGERPMMIN

LABEL: KEFADD_N_FASD_RPM_HIGH

LABEL: KEFADD_N_FASD_RPM_LOW

LABEL: KEFADD_P_FASD_BAROMETERLOW

LABEL: KEFADD_P_FASD_PURGE_MAP_HIGH

LABEL: KEFADD_T_FASD_COOLANTTEMPLOW

LABEL: KEFADD_T_FASD_COOLANTTEMPMIN

LABEL: KEFADD_T_FASD_DECIMALTIMESTEP

LABEL: KEFADD_T_FASD_IAT_LOW

LABEL: KEFADD_P_FASD_PURGE_MAP_LOW

LABEL: KE_IATD_SHORTED_LOW_THRESH

COMMENT: Time which the primary fuel level must remain above the threshold to turn off the xfer pump.
